Thank you. A picture together?

62
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:30,450
Okay, thanks.

63
00:05:38,570 --> 00:05:40,270
Go on.

64
00:05:53,170 --> 00:05:54,970
Do I look good?

65
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:57,490
Yes.

66
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:10,050
Jiang Jia.

67
00:06:10,050 --> 00:06:13,049
Senior Qianyu. Congrats on a successful performance.

68
00:06:13,049 --> 00:06:14,730
Thank you.

69
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:20,729
After you go abroad, we wouldn't see other again in a long time.

70
00:06:20,729 --> 00:06:22,330
I'm not good with words.

71
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:24,070
So...

72
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:31,250
I wrote something for you.

73
00:06:33,170 --> 00:06:34,870
Thank you.

74
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:37,969
I have a younger sister.

75
00:06:37,969 --> 00:06:41,309
She likes to put her emotions into words and pass letters to me too.

76
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:43,750
You remind me of her.

77
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:46,789
I don't know when we'd meet again.

78
00:06:46,790 --> 00:06:48,429
Hope you do well in your studies.

79
00:06:48,430 --> 00:06:52,110
Grow up sooner and meet your Mr. Right.

80
00:06:55,330 --> 00:06:58,630
I hope you'll continue to shine.

81
00:06:58,630 --> 00:07:05,410
Besides a bright future, I'd like to wish you a happy life.

82
00:07:05,410 --> 00:07:07,130
Thank you.

83
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,669
I just remembered.

84
00:07:09,670 --> 00:07:13,570
I made some typos in the letter.

85
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:15,950
I'll give it to you next time.

86
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:17,550
Okay.

87
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:48,370
If it's not meant to be yours, you can't force it.

88
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,870
Change into these.

89
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:55,510
Gu Ran.

90
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,530
Why are you here alone?

91
00:07:59,530 --> 00:08:01,370
Where are the others?

92
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:05,210
They're in there talking to Senior Qianyu.

93
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:08,250
Was it worth it?

94
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:11,290
Getting blisters from wearing ill-fitting shoes?

95
00:08:12,710 --> 00:08:15,789
It's the price of being pretty. You know nothing.

96
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:32,130
Do you know how many stars there are in the sky?

97
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:35,329
- Stars? 
 - Yeah.

98
00:08:35,329 --> 00:08:37,050
100 million?

99
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:43,430
At least 200 billion.

100
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:50,500
But among the billions of stars, no two are the same.

101
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,620
It's the same thing when they look at us.

102
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:54,620
They're probably also wondering.

103
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:58,580
How come there aren't any two humans alike out of so many?

104
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,960
You're the same.

105
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:05,999
The Jiang Jia I know is carefree.

106
00:09:05,999 --> 00:09:09,630
She doesn't stick to trifles and always stands up for herself

107
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:12,400
if she's wronged rather than swallow the bitterness.

108
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:15,720
She's rough around the edges and inconsiderate

109
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,840
but...

110
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:21,860
no matter what happens, she's always cheerful and positive.

111
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:24,160
Like an idiot.

112
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:27,480
Must you list out my flaws like that?

113
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:30,700
What I mean is,

114
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,220
you are you.

115
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:37,219
Although you're not anywhere perfect, you're still one of a kind.

116
00:09:37,219 --> 00:09:42,239
♫  slowly blew past your left ear and whispered something to you  ♫

117
00:09:42,239 --> 00:09:47,239
You don't have to wear ill-fitting shoes and pretend to be someone you're not.

118
00:09:47,239 --> 00:09:49,660
You're unique and shining bright.

119
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:53,680
♫  And there is a soul that is anxious when it's about to meet you  ♫

120
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:56,240
♫  What should I prepare?  ♫

121
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,819
♫  My palms are sweaty  ♫

122
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:04,860
♫  Does meeting me make you happy too?  ♫

123
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:10,320
♫  The summer breeze makes our hearts beat faster  ♫

124
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:14,820
♫  I dream of castles and colorful whirpools  ♫

125
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,300
So one failed confession is not that big of a deal.

126
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:20,160
You don't have to be so dejected.

127
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,660
I'm not dejected.

128
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:25,380
♫  Don't avoid my eyes anymore  ♫

129
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:27,739
Senior Qianyu said I was like his younger sister.

130
00:10:27,739 --> 00:10:30,960
To think of it, being his sister isn't that bad.

131
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:33,660
Maybe things will be different in the future.

132
00:10:33,660 --> 00:10:36,619
I've got a strong heart, you know?

133
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:39,120
Don't underestimate me.

134
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,439
Is that so?

135
00:10:41,439 --> 00:10:44,800
Then why did you cry when you failed the monthly math test?

136
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,720
Your heart isn't strong enough to endure failures in your studies?

137
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:50,180
Do you have to bring that up?

138
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,880
Why are you so jolly anyway?

139
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:58,250
Because...

140
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:01,780
I'm having midnight snacks later. I can't wait.

141
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:11,380
   

142
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:15,020
If I remember correctly, you guys have a class in the afternoon, right?

143
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:17,719
We can make it as long as we get there before 1:30 p.m.

144
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:21,700
If we didn't come, we'd feel uneasy in class.

145
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:24,659
Oh. Where's Jiang Jia?

146
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:35,000
The 1,000th star. It represents good luck.

147
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:41,740
Thank you.

148
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:47,540
When will you come back, Senior Qianyu?

149
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,579
At the end of the year. I'll be back when it snows in Jiangyi.

150
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:53,699
Hopefully, you'd be more mature when I'm back.

151
00:11:53,699 --> 00:11:55,000
Kiddo.

152
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,339
I'm only one year younger than you.

153
00:11:57,339 --> 00:11:59,599
And I've always been mature for my age.

154
00:11:59,599 --> 00:12:02,199
Remember? I always let you have the toys when we were kids.

155
00:12:02,199 --> 00:12:03,960
You only let me have the ones you didn't like.

156
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:07,619
♫  Love often carry a sense of regret  ♫ 
 ♫  Is it a mere passing or just a fleeting encounter?  ♫

157
00:12:07,619 --> 00:12:10,319
You never concede what you really like.

158
00:12:10,319 --> 00:12:12,539
♫  Yet you are always wandering by my side  ♫

159
00:12:12,539 --> 00:12:15,739
It's almost time. You guys should go. I have to pass security.

160
00:12:15,739 --> 00:12:19,800
♫  The summer rain always misses out on the falling leaves of Autumn  ♫

161
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:22,459
- Let's play basketball together when you're back. 
 - Sure.

162
00:12:22,459 --> 00:12:24,500
All the best.

163
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,720
I'll get going.

164
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,940
♫  I firmly believe that you'll take my hand once winter is over  ♫

165
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:28,259
Bye-bye.

166
00:12:28,259 --> 00:12:33,680
♫  I rather sit with you and enjoy the breeze than chasing after sunsets  ♫

167
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,439
Is it because I can't bear to see Senior Qianyu go?

168
00:12:35,439 --> 00:12:38,499
Why do I feel so anxious?

169
00:12:38,499 --> 00:12:41,459
Could it be because the final exam results will be announced later?

170
00:12:41,459 --> 00:12:43,739
The class will begin in 20 minutes.

171
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:45,440
♫  At any moment, anywhere  ♫

172
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:47,699
♫  My love for you is always there  ♫

173
00:12:47,699 --> 00:12:49,579
Don't just stand there. Run!

174
00:12:49,579 --> 00:12:55,480
♫  You occupy me, no one can take your place  ♫

175
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:59,259
♫  Your appearance brought along anticipation  ♫

176
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:02,539
♫  Let love change from dust to dependence  ♫

177
00:13:02,539 --> 00:13:06,720
♫  The most dazzling colors reside in our hearts  ♫

178
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:11,559
♫  Yours and mine  ♫

